{"cursor":"22131","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'collection agency' is a business that pursues payments of debts owed by\nindividuals or businesses. Most collection agencies operate as agents\nof creditors and collect debts for a fee or percentage of the total amount\nowed.\n\nThere are many types of collection agencies. First-party agencies are\noftentimes subsidiaries of the original company the debt is owed to. Third-\nparty agencies are separate companies contracted by a company to collect debts\non their behalf for a fee. Debt buyers purchase the debt at a percentage of its\nvalue, then attempt to collect it. Each country has its own rules and\nregulations regarding them.\n","linknr":327,"url":"Collection_agency","recorded":1362671601,"links":26,"instances":["remuneration"],"pdf":["http://www.freddiemac.com/creditsmart/pdf/68846_english_text.pdf","http://www.ftc.gov/bcp/edu/pubs/consumer/credit/cre27.pdf"],"categories":["Debt collection","Collection agencies","Financial services"],"headings":["First-party agencies","Third party agencies","Sale of debts","Debtors","Collection practices","Regulation of collection agencies","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["commission","remuneration"]],"members":["commission"],"related":["Debt","Creditor","Debt_buyer","Service_level_agreement","Fair_Debt_Collection_Practices_Act","Federal_Trade_Commission","Consumer_Credit_Act_1974","Office_of_Fair_Trading","Debt_buyer","Debtor","Kansas","Termination_of_employment","Dishonesty","Commission_(remuneration)","FDCPA","FDCPA","Identity_theft","Loan","Debt","Credit_record","Limitation_period","Credit_bureau","Alberta","British_Columbia","Manitoba","New_Brunswick","Newfoundland_and_Labrador","Nova_Scotia","Ontario","Pri